1
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:51,920
Please introduce yourself.

2
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,079
I'm Yan Ying,

3
00:00:54,399 --> 00:00:56,000
the General Defending the State of Qingyun.

4
00:00:56,439 --> 00:00:58,039
I'm good at strategy, riding and shooting.

5
00:00:58,799 --> 00:01:00,679
I've been guarding the border with my father since I was 15.

6
00:01:00,920 --> 00:01:01,880
I've been doing it for nine years.

7
00:01:02,399 --> 00:01:03,320
I've been leading troops for five years.

8
00:01:03,439 --> 00:01:04,439
I've been through hundreds of battles.

9
00:01:04,599 --> 00:01:05,599
I've been risking my life

10
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:08,000
to protect the people of Qingyun.

11
00:01:12,400 --> 00:01:12,920
Now,

12
00:01:13,120 --> 00:01:14,359
I have a new choice.

13
00:01:15,120 --> 00:01:16,640
I choose to stay in this world.

14
00:01:17,640 --> 00:01:19,280
Even though this world is

15
00:01:19,400 --> 00:01:20,799
completely unfamiliar to me,

16
00:01:22,200 --> 00:01:23,519
I came to your world

17
00:01:23,519 --> 00:01:24,319
not as a general,

18
00:01:24,640 --> 00:01:25,599
but I never abandoned my original intention.

19
00:01:26,280 --> 00:01:27,519
I came to apply for this job

20
00:01:27,879 --> 00:01:29,920
to continue to protect your world.

21
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:33,239
A man should establish a heart for the world,

22
00:01:33,439 --> 00:01:34,519
set a destiny for the people,

23
00:01:34,640 --> 00:01:35,959
continue the lost knowledge of the past,

24
00:01:36,120 --> 00:01:37,400
and bring peace to future generations.

25
00:01:38,200 --> 00:01:40,200
A woman should be the same.

26
00:02:02,319 --> 00:02:03,719
Oh my god!

27
00:02:04,239 --> 00:02:06,040
Where did you learn your kung fu?

28
00:02:07,799 --> 00:02:08,879
Are you okay?

29
00:02:27,280 --> 00:02:28,039
Have you found a job?

30
00:02:28,039 --> 00:02:28,520
Yes.

31
00:02:28,759 --> 00:02:29,639
What job?

32
00:02:31,479 --> 00:02:31,800
Well...

33
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,520
I promised to help a delivery guy

34
00:02:34,520 --> 00:02:35,520
deliver food for three days.

35
00:02:36,199 --> 00:02:36,759
In this way,

36
00:02:36,879 --> 00:02:39,039
he can get the full attendance bonus

37
00:02:39,039 --> 00:02:40,520
and pay his sister's tuition fees.

38
00:02:43,719 --> 00:02:45,599
Why do you have to deliver food by yourself?

39
00:02:45,800 --> 00:02:46,879
Let Chaika do it for you.

40
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,039
No.

41
00:02:48,319 --> 00:02:49,599
We had a deal.

42
00:02:50,400 --> 00:02:51,120
From now on,

43
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,840
I want to be self-reliant

44
00:02:53,039 --> 00:02:54,599
and find my own value in this world.

45
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,560
Delivering food is very meaningful to me.

46
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,400
Not only can I help that guy,

47
00:02:58,520 --> 00:03:00,080
but I can also deliver hot meals

48
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,479
to hungry people.

49
00:03:01,599 --> 00:03:02,199
I really like it.

50
00:03:03,319 --> 00:03:04,039
You're really something.

51
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:05,800
Let's go out for dinner.

52
00:03:09,199 --> 00:03:09,599
Let's go.

53
00:03:17,960 --> 00:03:18,280
Oh.

54
00:03:18,599 --> 00:03:19,479
Just have the takeout delivered.

55
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:20,759
Okay.

56
00:03:23,719 --> 00:03:24,120
Boss,

57
00:03:24,599 --> 00:03:27,000
Li Si's new book, "Dead End", is blowing up.

58
00:03:27,719 --> 00:03:28,919
The board decided

59
00:03:28,919 --> 00:03:31,000
to sign him back with our publishing house.

60
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,120
Alright, I got it.

61
00:03:32,199 --> 00:03:33,199
Go take a nap.

62
00:03:35,120 --> 00:03:35,599
Boss,

63
00:03:36,000 --> 00:03:37,400
I've been here for three years,

64
00:03:37,719 --> 00:03:39,360
and I've never heard of a nap.

65
00:03:41,560 --> 00:03:42,840
Excuse me,

66
00:03:44,759 --> 00:03:46,960
your takeout has arrived.

67
00:03:47,280 --> 00:03:48,120
Just give it to me.

68
00:03:48,400 --> 00:03:48,759
Hey,

69
00:03:49,199 --> 00:03:50,400
can't you recognize my girlfriend?

70
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,039
Ah?

71
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:55,680
With my salary, how can I afford so much?

72
00:04:00,759 --> 00:04:01,840
Why did you order so much?

73
00:04:02,520 --> 00:04:03,400
To eat with you.

74
00:04:03,400 --> 00:04:04,280
I'm running late.

75
00:04:04,280 --> 00:04:05,919
I still have a lot of deliveries to make.

76
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:07,560
Oh.

77
00:04:09,080 --> 00:04:11,159
But my hand isn't fully healed yet.

78
00:04:11,560 --> 00:04:12,759
Not healed yet?

79
00:04:12,879 --> 00:04:13,319
Yeah.

80
00:04:19,399 --> 00:04:20,439
Ah.

81
00:04:21,399 --> 00:04:22,120
Ah.

82
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:29,879
Still haven't finished swallowing.

83
00:04:32,399 --> 00:04:33,160
Keep eating.

84
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:35,680
I'm off.

85
00:04:50,600 --> 00:04:51,120
Hello.

86
00:04:51,120 --> 00:04:53,519
This is the Moon Publishing House under Wen Sheng Group.

87
00:04:56,519 --> 00:04:57,879
Moon Publishing House

88
00:05:00,480 --> 00:05:02,040
The response to your new book, Dead End, is very good.

89
00:05:02,240 --> 00:05:04,360
Our publishing house is considering reworking with you.

90
00:05:04,639 --> 00:05:05,720
If you are also willing,

91
00:05:05,720 --> 00:05:06,759
we can meet again

92
00:05:06,759 --> 00:05:07,680
to discuss the contract.

93
00:05:14,879 --> 00:05:15,439
Very good.

94
00:05:16,240 --> 00:05:17,600
I'll wait to see your sincerity.

95
00:05:41,439 --> 00:05:42,399
Hello.

96
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:43,480
Your takeout.

97
00:05:44,079 --> 00:05:45,680
Can you help me take it to the rooftop?

98
00:05:46,240 --> 00:05:47,040
Rooftop?

99
00:05:47,720 --> 00:05:48,000
Right.

100
00:05:50,639 --> 00:05:51,879
Oh, alright.

101
00:06:00,720 --> 00:06:02,199
Hello, your takeout.

102
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:07,800
Xiao Chengjing?

103
00:06:13,279 --> 00:06:14,279
Oh, sorry,

104
00:06:14,279 --> 00:06:15,360
I mistook you for someone else.

105
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:16,879
I'll leave your takeout here.

106
00:06:16,879 --> 00:06:17,639
Help yourself.

107
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,000
Yan Ying,

108
00:06:31,279 --> 00:06:32,560
this place is very different

109
00:06:32,959 --> 00:06:33,639
from our home.

110
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,079
Yes.

111
00:06:37,399 --> 00:06:39,279
How did you get here?

112
00:06:39,839 --> 00:06:41,439
Why did you use someone else's identity?

113
00:06:42,920 --> 00:06:43,519
I don't know.

114
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:45,160
I woke up

115
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:46,519
and found myself here.

116
00:06:47,279 --> 00:06:48,560
I happened to meet Li Si.

117
00:06:49,639 --> 00:06:50,800
He happened to

118
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,600
want to end his life.

119
00:06:54,600 --> 00:06:55,839
So I took his place.

120
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:01,199
Is this wine?

121
00:07:02,319 --> 00:07:03,240
It tastes weird.

122
00:07:04,639 --> 00:07:05,759
I just

123
00:07:06,000 --> 00:07:06,680
I don't like it.

124
00:07:07,480 --> 00:07:08,480
It's good to adapt.

125
00:07:13,639 --> 00:07:15,199
But I still like Osmanthus Wine.

126
00:07:16,399 --> 00:07:17,439
It seems you've adapted well.

127
00:07:18,839 --> 00:07:20,600
How did you feel when you first arrived?

128
00:07:24,519 --> 00:07:25,360
That day,

129
00:07:26,319 --> 00:07:27,439
I was also standing here,

130
00:07:28,639 --> 00:07:30,040
looking at this world.

131
00:07:30,879 --> 00:07:32,279
I didn't know who I was,

132
00:07:33,199 --> 00:07:33,920
where I was,

133
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:35,959
or where I should go.

134
00:07:36,879 --> 00:07:38,199
It was as if my existence

135
00:07:38,920 --> 00:07:40,600
could be easily erased at any moment.

136
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:44,720
as if I had never existed.

137
00:07:47,639 --> 00:07:48,120
And then?

138
00:07:49,199 --> 00:07:50,000
How did you get here?

139
00:07:55,639 --> 00:07:56,920
I just got here.

140
00:08:00,480 --> 00:08:00,959
Yan Ying,

141
00:08:01,680 --> 00:08:02,560
you seem to have changed

142
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:04,120
quite a bit.

143
00:08:06,000 --> 00:08:06,839
Actually,

144
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:10,399
I still can't let go of some things.

145
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,519
But I don't know how to deal with them.

146
00:08:20,720 --> 00:08:21,959
We are both characters in a book.

147
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:23,879
Our fate is determined by heaven.

148
00:08:25,079 --> 00:08:27,279
This situation is a new beginning.

149
00:08:29,040 --> 00:08:30,160
I've let go of the past

150
00:08:30,360 --> 00:08:31,360
and am ready to start over.

151
00:08:32,559 --> 00:08:34,360
Don't you welcome me?

152
00:08:35,320 --> 00:08:36,519
Do we still need to be trapped

153
00:08:36,519 --> 00:08:37,840
in that non-existent world?

154
00:08:44,440 --> 00:08:45,440
In this foreign land,

155
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:47,759
I can only rely on you from now on.

156
00:08:53,840 --> 00:08:54,320
Okay.

157
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,440
It's fortunate to reunite.
